---
description: How tests are organized and how to extend them safely
---

# Test stack

- Unit/integration: Vitest (Node, TZ=UTC). Config in app/vitest.* and scripts in app/package.json
- E2E: Playwright (public and authed projects), with accessibility checks and visual snapshots
- Forecast: Dedicated TS test runner (tsx) that executes forecast scenarios and performance checks

# Where tests live

- API routes: app/server/api/__tests__/*.test.ts — comprehensive coverage of endpoints (auth, accounts, registers, entries, budgets, categories, reports, reconciliations, tasks, Plaid, MFA, etc.)
- Services: app/server/services/**/__tests__ — forecast, matching, RSA/JWT, Plaid sync/enrichment, budget/category cloning, reports, etc.
- Libs/schemas: app/lib/__tests__ and app/schema/__tests__
- Stores/pages: app/stores/__tests__ and app/pages/__tests__ (smoke/simple)
- E2E: app/tests/e2e/** (fixtures, setup, specs, snapshots). Public and authed projects each have separate suites and baselines

# Running tests

- All: pnpm test (Vitest, TZ=UTC)
- Coverage: pnpm test:coverage; artifacts are LCOV for Sonar when invoked in sonar.yml
- Forecast engine: pnpm test:forecast, test:forecast:unit, test:forecast:integration, test:forecast:performance
- E2E: pnpm test:e2e (local), or the manual staging snapshot updater workflow for Linux baselines

# Environment for tests

- Minimal env used in CI (pr.yml): DATABASE_URL for local MySQL in CI, DEPLOY_ENV=local, DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY dummy, PLAID_* dummy
- Prisma client must be generated before tests that import Prisma types: pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate
- Tests generally mock integrations; real MySQL/Redis are not required for Vitest by default suites

# Adding tests

- For new endpoints: add Vitest route tests in app/server/api/__tests__ covering auth, input validation, domain branching, and error mapping
- For new services: unit tests for core logic, plus integration where DB state is material
- For forecast changes: extend scenarios and regression snapshots under server/services/forecast/__tests__
- For UI flows: add Playwright specs and update visual snapshots (local vs staging Linux baselines differ; use the staging workflow to update CI baselines)

# Debugging tests

- Run a single file: vitest run path/to/test.ts
- Forecast debug: set DEBUG=forecast:* for verbose logs where supported by the services
- E2E: playwright test --ui or --debug to inspect failures; review generated screenshots under -snapshots directories
